00:19:08.389 --> 00:19:10.559
GIRL: Hey!

519
00:19:08.389 --> 00:19:10.559
Oh. no.

520
00:19:11.893 --> 00:19:13.059
Thank you so much.

521
00:19:13.127 --> 00:19:14.426
Oh. everything
was wonderful. Mary.

522
00:19:14.495 --> 00:19:17.063
I must have the name
of your caterer. So yummy.

523
00:19:17.132 --> 00:19:18.464
Oh. no.
I made everything myself.

524
00:19:18.533 --> 00:19:20.700
I think people appreciate
the personal touch.

525
00:19:20.769 --> 00:19:21.835
You cooked?

526
00:19:21.903 --> 00:19:24.136
Oh. Mary. how could you?
What were you thinking?

527
00:19:24.205 --> 00:19:25.972
Now we'll all have to do that.

528
00:19:26.040 --> 00:19:27.439
And not all of us are you.

529
00:19:27.508 --> 00:19:30.877
Anyway. congratulations
on a successful event.

530
00:19:30.946 --> 00:19:32.044
Phone for you. It's him.

531
00:19:32.113 --> 00:19:33.416
Oh.

532
00:19:35.116 --> 00:19:36.785
Bye.

533
00:19:35.116 --> 00:19:36.785
WOMEN: Bye.

534
00:19:38.085 --> 00:19:40.019
Hey. honey. they're almost gone.

535
00:19:40.088 --> 00:19:41.687
It's safe to come home.

536
00:19:41.756 --> 00:19:44.391
Hey. listen. since we're leaving
so early in the morning tomorrow

537
00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:45.929
let's just eat out. and...

538
00:19:51.132 --> 00:19:53.833
Stephen?

539
00:19:53.902 --> 00:19:55.201
Ste...

540
00:19:55.269 --> 00:19:58.204
Stephen. it took forever
to plan this trip

541
00:19:58.273 --> 00:20:00.576
and we both really
need a vacation.

542
00:20:01.542 --> 00:20:03.712
Yeah... No.
there has to be some way.

543
00:20:11.919 --> 00:20:13.589
All right.

544
00:20:14.690 --> 00:20:16.555
Okay. I'll call
the travel agent.

545
00:20:16.623 --> 00:20:20.429
I guess. uh. Venice
will still be there.

546
00:20:20.995 --> 00:20:22.294
When are you coming home?

547
00:20:22.363 --> 00:20:24.733
Oh. okay. then I won't wait up.

548
00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:27.703
All right. bye.

549
00:20:33.641 --> 00:20:36.308
That goddamn office
is sucking the life out of him.

550
00:20:36.377 --> 00:20:37.910
Well. something definitely is.

551
00:20:37.979 --> 00:20:39.478
Sylvie. Come on.

552
00:20:39.546 --> 00:20:41.513
We didn't mean
to be listening in.

553
00:20:41.582 --> 00:20:43.916
No. no. it's okay. Thank you so
much for coming today.

554
00:20:43.985 --> 00:20:45.417
It meant a lot to me.

555
00:20:45.486 --> 00:20:48.453
Are you gonna be okay?
I would stay. but we carpooled.

556
00:20:48.522 --> 00:20:51.057
I'm so sorry. I've got
the little ones at home.

557
00:20:51.126 --> 00:20:52.191
No. no. I'm fine.

558
00:20:52.260 --> 00:20:53.626
I'm gonna be fine.

559
00:20:53.695 --> 00:20:54.960
Mwah.

560
00:20:55.029 --> 00:20:56.763
Mwah.

561
00:20:56.832 --> 00:20:58.467
Okay.

562
00:21:01.803 --> 00:21:03.303
Goddamn it.

563
00:21:03.371 --> 00:21:05.237
[♪♪♪]

564
00:21:05.306 --> 00:21:07.306
Ned. you gotta back me on this.

565
00:21:07.374 --> 00:21:09.708
It's time to stop talking down
to our readers.

566
00:21:09.777 --> 00:21:12.278
That's the way <i>Cachet</i>
is gonna distinguish itself.

567
00:21:12.346 --> 00:21:14.713
You talk about
branding the magazine.

568
00:21:14.782 --> 00:21:19.218
How about we become the
thinking woman's fashion book?

569
00:21:19.287 --> 00:21:21.453
Bring on
the provocative writers.

570
00:21:21.522 --> 00:21:23.960
We stop putting little Hollywood
twits on the cover.

571
00:21:25.460 --> 00:21:27.994
Yes. I know
the twits sell. but. Ned.

572
00:21:28.062 --> 00:21:29.028
you hired me for a reason.

573
00:21:29.097 --> 00:21:30.562
Let me do my job.

574
00:21:30.631 --> 00:21:33.400
This time next year.
you'll look like a genius.

575
00:21:33.469 --> 00:21:34.701
Mary's on three.

576
00:21:34.770 --> 00:21:37.703
Ned. I got Ralph Lauren
on the line.

577
00:21:37.772 --> 00:21:39.442
I gotta go.

578
00:21:40.341 --> 00:21:42.675
So how was lunch with Dad?

579
00:21:42.744 --> 00:21:43.909
Huh?

580
00:21:43.977 --> 00:21:46.379
How does it feel to be head
of your own design house?

581
00:21:46.448 --> 00:21:48.848
He fired me.

582
00:21:46.448 --> 00:21:48.848
<i>What?</i>

583
00:21:48.917 --> 00:21:50.215
Yeah. my own father.

584
00:21:50.284 --> 00:21:52.552
He said I was spreading myself
too thin

585
00:21:52.621 --> 00:21:54.486
and that it showed in my work.

586
00:21:54.555 --> 00:21:56.788
Excuse me. but designing
the perfect little frock

587
00:21:56.857 --> 00:22:00.092
for a woman to wear home
from hip-replacement surgery

588
00:22:00.161 --> 00:22:01.861
is not exactly my work.

589
00:22:01.929 --> 00:22:03.662
Oh. honey.

590
00:22:03.730 --> 00:22:06.165
Come to my office. the Grey
Goose rep was just here.

591
00:22:06.234 --> 00:22:08.535
We'll open a bottle and bitch
about the men in our lives

592
00:22:08.604 --> 00:22:09.735
who don't believe in us.

593
00:22:09.804 --> 00:22:11.503
Uh. what?
Is Ned riding you again?

594
00:22:11.572 --> 00:22:13.473
Oh. I mean.
that's just absolutely absurd.

595
00:22:13.541 --> 00:22:15.574
That must feel terrible. Oh!

596
00:22:15.643 --> 00:22:17.343
Why doesn't he just trust
your vision?

597
00:22:17.411 --> 00:22:19.879
Well. it's a crisis
of confidence.

598
00:22:19.947 --> 00:22:20.880
I can feel it.

599
00:22:20.948 --> 00:22:22.582
I need to pull a couple
of great writers

600
00:22:22.650 --> 00:22:24.616
onto this magazine. and fast.

601
00:22:24.685 --> 00:22:27.119
<i>Well. you can do that.
Stop at nothing.</i>

602
00:22:27.188 --> 00:22:29.221
I love you. you know that?

603
00:22:29.290 --> 00:22:31.157
Whoa. well. you wouldn't
if you saw me.

604
00:22:31.226 --> 00:22:32.624
My hair looks terrible.

605
00:22:32.693 --> 00:22:35.494
Could you get me into Saks
for a haircut? Is that okay?

606
00:22:35.563 --> 00:22:37.897
Don't go to Saks.
They'll butcher you.

607
00:22:37.966 --> 00:22:40.299
Hey! Hey!

608
00:22:40.368 --> 00:22:41.600
Wait. what
are you talking about?

609
00:22:41.669 --> 00:22:44.270
That woman just did
the rudest thing.

610
00:22:44.339 --> 00:22:45.638
Your hair always looks great.

611
00:22:45.707 --> 00:22:47.206
<i>Anyway. love you. mean it. bye.</i>

612
00:22:47.274 --> 00:22:48.841
Mary...

613
00:22:47.274 --> 00:22:48.841
[PHONE LINE CLICKS]

614
00:22:48.910 --> 00:22:50.914
Mary?

615
00:22:52.047 --> 00:22:53.116
Women.

616
00:22:55.183 --> 00:22:56.885
[PHONE RINGING]

617
00:23:00.755 --> 00:23:04.023
Hello. I... I'm Mary Haines.
and my friend Sylvie Fowler

618
00:23:04.092 --> 00:23:05.591
called ahead for me.

619
00:23:05.659 --> 00:23:08.027
Yes. she did. We can squeeze you
in. but not for an hour.

620
00:23:08.096 --> 00:23:09.929
I'm really sorry.

621
00:23:08.096 --> 00:23:09.929
Oh.

622
00:23:09.998 --> 00:23:13.467
Oh. well. can I get
a manicure while I wait?

623
00:23:13.535 --> 00:23:15.068
Let me check.

624
00:23:13.535 --> 00:23:15.068
Okay.

625
00:23:15.136 --> 00:23:16.702
Let's see.

626
00:23:16.771 --> 00:23:19.072
Okay. Tanya's
had a cancellation.

627
00:23:19.141 --> 00:23:20.472
Great.

628
00:23:20.541 --> 00:23:22.309
First table. straight back.

629
00:23:20.541 --> 00:23:22.309
Okay. thank you.

630
00:23:22.377 --> 00:23:23.876
Oh.

631
00:23:23.945 --> 00:23:25.915
Okay. Tanya?

632
00:23:33.921 --> 00:23:34.687
Tanya?

633
00:23:34.756 --> 00:23:36.589
Hi. they told me
to come back here.

634
00:23:36.658 --> 00:23:38.794
Oh. sure. have a seat.

635
00:23:40.194 --> 00:23:42.728
Well. let's have a look.

636
00:23:42.797 --> 00:23:44.630
Oh. my. what have we done
to ourselves?

637
00:23:44.699 --> 00:23:46.232
Oh. I re-tiled my bathroom.

638
00:23:46.301 --> 00:23:47.367
Ha. Seriously?

639
00:23:46.301 --> 00:23:47.367
Yeah.

640
00:23:47.436 --> 00:23:48.935
Oh. God. Oh.

641
00:23:49.003 --> 00:23:50.870
Oh. I was thinking
about something neutral.

642
00:23:50.939 --> 00:23:53.172
Wanna maybe take a walk
on the wild side?

643
00:23:53.241 --> 00:23:55.174
How about this? Jungle Red.

644
00:23:55.243 --> 00:23:57.276
That's a little too much for me.

645
00:23:57.345 --> 00:23:58.378
How about this? This is nice.

646
00:23:58.446 --> 00:24:00.380
French Fawn. whatever.

647
00:24:00.449 --> 00:24:01.951
Okay.

648
00:24:00.449 --> 00:24:01.951
[SIGHS]

649
00:24:04.485 --> 00:24:05.718
What's that perfume
you're wearing?

650
00:24:05.787 --> 00:24:07.553
It's something my husband
gave me.

651
00:24:07.621 --> 00:24:10.056
Oh. where have
I smelled that before?

652
00:24:10.125 --> 00:24:12.625
Oh. I know. That's the same
stuff that my friend wears.

653
00:24:12.693 --> 00:24:14.994
She works
the perfume counter downstairs.

654
00:24:15.063 --> 00:24:16.029
Expensive stuff.

655
00:24:16.097 --> 00:24:18.297
But she's got expensive taste.
that one.

656
00:24:18.365 --> 00:24:19.866
Her name's Crystal Allen.

657
00:24:18.365 --> 00:24:19.866
Who?

658
00:24:19.934 --> 00:24:21.534
My friend
at the perfume counter.

659
00:24:21.602 --> 00:24:22.969
That girl needs
a man with money.

660
00:24:23.038 --> 00:24:25.839
She's got one now too.
Married. though.

661
00:24:25.907 --> 00:24:27.907
Narciso Rodriguez
is just amazing.

662
00:24:27.976 --> 00:24:30.176
The guy she hooked.
his picture's always

663
00:24:30.245 --> 00:24:31.710
in the business pages.

664
00:24:31.778 --> 00:24:34.079
For Crystal. that's like
the classifieds for a husband.

665
00:24:34.148 --> 00:24:36.315
I can never remember that
guy's name. What's his name?

666
00:24:36.384 --> 00:24:39.719
Everyone knows him. That's
a beautiful ring. by the way.

667
00:24:39.788 --> 00:24:41.654
Oh. thank you.

668
00:24:39.788 --> 00:24:41.654
On the wrong hand. though.

669
00:24:41.722 --> 00:24:43.756
No. it's the right hand.
My girlfriends gave it to me.

670
00:24:43.825 --> 00:24:45.524
We gave each other one
last Christmas.

671
00:24:45.593 --> 00:24:48.327
Haines. that's his name.
Stephen Haines.

672
00:24:48.396 --> 00:24:49.463
I was there when she met him.

673
00:24:49.531 --> 00:24:51.363
Oh. boy. what a performance.

674
00:24:51.432 --> 00:24:53.432
This Haines guy walks up
to the counter

675
00:24:53.501 --> 00:24:55.501
serious type. expensive suit.

676
00:24:55.570 --> 00:24:57.103
good-looking.
little thinning on top

677
00:24:57.172 --> 00:24:59.672
and he says he wants to buy
some perfume for his wife.

678
00:24:59.740 --> 00:25:01.808
"Well. what type of woman
is she?" Crystal says.

679
00:25:01.877 --> 00:25:03.743
And he says. "The kind that
smells like soap."

680
00:25:03.811 --> 00:25:05.377
Which I thought
was really sweet.

681
00:25:05.446 --> 00:25:06.845
But for Crystal.
this is a challenge.

682
00:25:06.914 --> 00:25:09.816
So then she says. "Would you
prefer something sexier?"

683
00:25:09.885 --> 00:25:12.051
And she runs her eyes
up and down him

684
00:25:12.119 --> 00:25:14.386
the way a big cat looks
at a slow wildebeest.

685
00:25:14.455 --> 00:25:15.755
I mean. I felt kind
of bad for the guy.

686
00:25:15.823 --> 00:25:17.223
He didn't stand a chance.

687
00:25:17.292 --> 00:25:20.593
So then she picks up the tester
bottle of Jezebel...

688
00:25:20.662 --> 00:25:21.794
That's the stuff you're wearing.

689
00:25:21.863 --> 00:25:23.562
...And she sprays it
on her wrist

690
00:25:23.631 --> 00:25:25.264
and in the crook of her arm
for him to smell

691
00:25:25.333 --> 00:25:26.799
and he starts sniffing around.

692
00:25:26.868 --> 00:25:28.801
Well. I guess he liked
it more than he planned.

693
00:25:28.870 --> 00:25:30.069
I mean. to tell you the truth.

694
00:25:30.138 --> 00:25:31.804
I think this was
a big game for Crystal.

695
00:25:31.873 --> 00:25:33.438
Until he took
out his credit card.

696
00:25:33.507 --> 00:25:35.078
and then she recognized
his name.

697
00:25:35.777 --> 00:25:36.842
And then what happened?

698
00:25:36.911 --> 00:25:38.544
Well. then she really
pursued him.

699
00:25:38.613 --> 00:25:40.112
Then they just started
seeing each other.

700
00:25:40.181 --> 00:25:42.849
He takes her for nice dinners.
buys her clothes.

701
00:25:42.918 --> 00:25:44.517
Sends her flowers in a vase.

702
00:25:44.586 --> 00:25:45.585
You know. the kind you keep.

703
00:25:45.654 --> 00:25:47.924
I don't think that...

704
00:25:49.791 --> 00:25:52.295
I don't think that. um...

705
00:25:53.395 --> 00:25:54.894
I'm...

706
00:25:54.963 --> 00:25:58.197
I... I just remembered
that I have to go somewhere.

707
00:25:58.265 --> 00:26:00.866
Oh. I... I'm so sorry.
Was I talking too much again?

708
00:26:00.935 --> 00:26:02.969
You know. I... I just try
to entertain my clients

709
00:26:03.038 --> 00:26:05.004
when they're sitting
here. Mrs...?

710
00:26:05.073 --> 00:26:06.042
Haines.

711
00:26:08.310 --> 00:26:09.642
Oh. God.

712
00:26:09.711 --> 00:26:10.877
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

713
00:26:10.946 --> 00:26:13.212
I'm so. so sorry.
I... I had no idea.

714
00:26:13.281 --> 00:26:15.949
Oh. me and my big mouth.
Is there anything I could do...?

715
00:26:16.017 --> 00:26:17.551
No. just stop telling
that story.

716
00:26:17.619 --> 00:26:18.685
Oh. sure. sure.

717
00:26:17.619 --> 00:26:18.685
I mean it.

718
00:26:18.753 --> 00:26:19.852
I'll never mention it again.

719
00:26:19.921 --> 00:26:23.192
I promise. I promise.
Mrs. Haines.

720
00:26:24.559 --> 00:26:26.593
Donna.

721
00:26:26.662 --> 00:26:28.861
Good dirt.

722
00:26:28.930 --> 00:26:31.831
Hello. it's Mary
for Sylvie again.

723
00:26:31.900 --> 00:26:34.166
Is she still in that meeting?

724
00:26:34.235 --> 00:26:36.035
Yes. if you could please
have her call me

725
00:26:36.104 --> 00:26:38.741
as soon as she
gets out. thank you.

726
00:26:41.075 --> 00:26:42.241
Am I late?

727
00:26:42.309 --> 00:26:43.676
I... I'm sorry. Mom.

728
00:26:43.745 --> 00:26:45.745
I heard what happened.

729
00:26:45.813 --> 00:26:47.580
Your father is a real shit.

730
00:26:47.649 --> 00:26:49.048
I ordered you a gimlet.

731
00:26:49.117 --> 00:26:51.050
I know. you don't drink
in the afternoon

732
00:26:51.118 --> 00:26:55.122
but you will eventually.
so why not start now?

733
00:26:55.191 --> 00:26:55.855
[HUMS]

734
00:26:55.923 --> 00:26:57.824
You wanna see a bad face lift?

735
00:26:57.893 --> 00:27:00.093
Helen Danvers. 2 o'clock.

736
00:27:00.161 --> 00:27:04.598
She looks like she's re-entering
the Earth's atmosphere.

737
00:27:04.666 --> 00:27:06.632
Honey. what can I do?

738
00:27:06.701 --> 00:27:07.867
Do you want me to punish Daddy?

739
00:27:07.936 --> 00:27:10.537
Mom. Stephen's having an affair.

740
00:27:10.606 --> 00:27:12.238
What?

741
00:27:12.307 --> 00:27:14.539
I can't believe those words
came out of my mouth.

742
00:27:14.608 --> 00:27:15.942
That just makes me sick
to my stomach.

743
00:27:16.011 --> 00:27:17.477
Who is she. one of your friends?

744
00:27:17.546 --> 00:27:21.284
No. she sells perfume at Saks.

745
00:27:22.283 --> 00:27:23.182
She's a spritzer girl?

746
00:27:23.251 --> 00:27:25.184
I mean. how could
I not have known?

747
00:27:25.253 --> 00:27:29.688
Three months ago.
he bought cowboy boots.

748
00:27:29.757 --> 00:27:31.525
I just can't believe
this is happening to me.

749
00:27:31.593 --> 00:27:35.294
I thought we were... happy.

750
00:27:35.363 --> 00:27:36.629
What are you going to do?

751
00:27:36.697 --> 00:27:37.863
What do you mean.
what am I gonna to do?

752
00:27:37.932 --> 00:27:39.398
I'm gonna tell him to move out.

753
00:27:39.466 --> 00:27:40.700
Well. that's not very smart.

754
00:27:40.769 --> 00:27:42.701
Someone once said

755
00:27:42.770 --> 00:27:44.971
that when you don't know
what to do. do nothing.

756
00:27:45.039 --> 00:27:49.874
Mom. my husband of 13 years
is having an affair.

757
00:27:49.943 --> 00:27:52.345
I mean. do they talk about
me when they're in bed?

758
00:27:52.414 --> 00:27:53.813
Do they laugh at me?

759
00:27:53.882 --> 00:27:55.615
I mean. please don't tell me
to pretend

760
00:27:55.684 --> 00:27:56.616
that nothing happened.

761
00:27:56.685 --> 00:27:58.154
You have no idea how this feels.

762
00:28:02.424 --> 00:28:05.158
Well. let me try.

763
00:28:05.226 --> 00:28:10.830
It feels like someone
kicked you in the stomach.

764
00:28:10.899 --> 00:28:13.633
It feels like your heart
stopped beating.

765
00:28:13.702 --> 00:28:15.001
It feels like that dream.

766
00:28:15.069 --> 00:28:16.836
You know. the one where
you're falling

767
00:28:16.905 --> 00:28:18.771
and you want so desperately
to wake up

768
00:28:18.840 --> 00:28:20.139
before you hit the ground.

769
00:28:20.208 --> 00:28:21.841
but it's all out
of your control.

770
00:28:21.910 --> 00:28:25.712
You can't trust
anything anymore.

771
00:28:25.781 --> 00:28:28.447
No one is who they say they are.

772
00:28:28.516 --> 00:28:30.049
Your life is changed forever.

773
00:28:30.118 --> 00:28:35.455
And the only thing to come
out of the whole ugly experience

774
00:28:35.523 --> 00:28:38.224
is no one will ever be able

775
00:28:38.292 --> 00:28:40.329
to break your heart
like that again.

776
