1541
00:57:14.309 --> 00:57:15.241
Climb higher.

1542
00:57:15.309 --> 00:57:17.177
Can't we take a break?

1543
00:57:17.245 --> 00:57:18.744
No breaks.

1544
00:57:18.812 --> 00:57:21.080
What are the most feared
words in the English language?

1545
00:57:21.149 --> 00:57:22.249
Pool party.

1546
00:57:22.317 --> 00:57:23.516
Keep climbing.

1547
00:57:23.585 --> 00:57:25.854
[♪♪♪]

1548
00:57:28.489 --> 00:57:31.858
Wait a minute.
Let... Let me down. okay?

1549
00:57:31.926 --> 00:57:33.292
Thanks.

1550
00:57:33.360 --> 00:57:35.428
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

1551
00:57:35.496 --> 00:57:37.429
Hey. Bailey Smith. right?

1552
00:57:37.498 --> 00:57:39.599
Sylvie Fowler.
We met at the MTV Awards.

1553
00:57:39.668 --> 00:57:41.766
Oh. right. right. right.

1554
00:57:41.835 --> 00:57:45.371
So how are things
in the. uh. hot seat at <i>Cachet?</i>

1555
00:57:45.439 --> 00:57:47.472
Well. I'm not gonna be happy

1556
00:57:47.541 --> 00:57:49.942
until I take a nice. big chunk
out of <i>Vogue.</i>

1557
00:57:50.011 --> 00:57:50.776
[CHUCKLES]

1558
00:57:50.845 --> 00:57:52.678
You know how I'm gonna do that?

1559
00:57:50.845 --> 00:57:52.678
How?

1560
00:57:52.747 --> 00:57:55.614
By putting star writers
on the magazine. like you.

1561
00:57:55.682 --> 00:57:58.151
Oh. well.
that is a nice compliment.

1562
00:57:58.219 --> 00:57:59.753
but I'm not for sale.

1563
00:57:59.821 --> 00:58:01.453
I'm really happy at <i>The Post.</i>

1564
00:58:01.522 --> 00:58:03.022
Excuse me. but I don't know why.

1565
00:58:03.090 --> 00:58:05.524
You made a reputation
writing brilliant profiles

1566
00:58:05.593 --> 00:58:08.528
and now you're writing gossip
for a tabloid.

1567
00:58:08.597 --> 00:58:10.897
Wait. I am syndicated.

1568
00:58:10.966 --> 00:58:13.266
I don't have to worry
about money anymore.

1569
00:58:13.334 --> 00:58:16.936
You know. anyway. I... I... I
write about people. not fashion.

1570
00:58:17.005 --> 00:58:18.871
That's exactly
what I want you to do.

1571
00:58:18.939 --> 00:58:22.074
Write about interesting people
in your own irreverent way.

1572
00:58:22.143 --> 00:58:23.475
You'll sell magazines.

1573
00:58:23.544 --> 00:58:26.712
I hear your circulation's down.

1574
00:58:26.781 --> 00:58:30.153
and didn't you have some
staff defections last week?

1575
00:58:31.519 --> 00:58:33.923
Some people
can't take the hills.

1576
00:58:35.089 --> 00:58:36.823
You know. um.

1577
00:58:36.891 --> 00:58:40.693
I would consider
doing some pieces for you.

1578
00:58:40.762 --> 00:58:43.196
but I would need something
in return.

1579
00:58:43.264 --> 00:58:45.198
Well. you name it.

1580
00:58:45.266 --> 00:58:47.033
Yeah?

1581
00:58:45.266 --> 00:58:47.033
Yeah.

1582
00:58:47.102 --> 00:58:49.635
Well. I'm doing
a series of columns

1583
00:58:49.704 --> 00:58:51.871
on high-profile
New York marriages.

1584
00:58:51.939 --> 00:58:52.805
Oh.

1585
00:58:52.874 --> 00:58:55.975
I hear one of them's
breaking up.

1586
00:58:56.044 --> 00:58:57.677
Oh. Oh.

1587
00:58:57.746 --> 00:58:59.078
You know who I'm talking about.

1588
00:58:59.147 --> 00:59:02.348
I don't know anything.
and who cares. anyway?

1589
00:59:02.417 --> 00:59:04.050
Oh. come on.

1590
00:59:04.118 --> 00:59:08.754
Messy divorces sell more papers
than presidential campaigns.

1591
00:59:08.822 --> 00:59:10.855
It sounds like you've
already written the story.

1592
00:59:10.924 --> 00:59:13.258
What do you need me for?

1593
00:59:10.924 --> 00:59:13.258
You know I need confirmation

1594
00:59:13.327 --> 00:59:15.795
from some ironclad source.

1595
00:59:15.864 --> 00:59:18.731
I'm sorry. I can't help you.

1596
00:59:18.799 --> 00:59:21.834
Just because you wouldn't do
a favor for me

1597
00:59:21.903 --> 00:59:24.538
doesn't mean I won't
do one for you.

1598
00:59:24.606 --> 00:59:26.671
One of my spies

1599
00:59:26.740 --> 00:59:29.808
said they saw
your publisher last night

1600
00:59:29.876 --> 00:59:33.346
having dinner with Talia Greene
from <i>Harper's Bazaar.</i>

1601
00:59:33.415 --> 00:59:34.681
Wait.

1602
00:59:34.750 --> 00:59:37.651
I am not worried. okay?

1603
00:59:37.719 --> 00:59:39.218
Ned wouldn't replace me.

1604
00:59:39.287 --> 00:59:42.587
He's completely committed
to my vision for the magazine.

1605
00:59:42.656 --> 00:59:45.023
Sure. I'm... I'm sure.
But it's just that

1606
00:59:45.091 --> 00:59:48.661
I... I... I heard that there was
some heavy wooing going on.

1607
00:59:48.730 --> 00:59:51.164
Bailey. do not print that. okay?

1608
00:59:51.232 --> 00:59:54.000
What little staff I have left
would smell blood.

1609
00:59:54.069 --> 00:59:56.602
It would completely destroy
my credibility at <i>Cachet.</i>

1610
00:59:56.671 --> 00:59:58.037
and then I really am
out the door.

1611
00:59:58.105 --> 01:00:00.006
I know.
It's incredible. isn't it.

1612
01:00:00.075 --> 01:00:02.207
how a little piece of gossip
like that

1613
01:00:02.276 --> 01:00:06.746
has the potential to actually
unravel an entire career.

1614
01:00:06.815 --> 01:00:09.182
Because really.
when you think about it.

1615
01:00:09.250 --> 01:00:12.121
where would you go
if you left <i>Cachet?</i>

1616
01:00:13.755 --> 01:00:15.358
[CAMERA CLICKING]

1617
01:00:18.793 --> 01:00:22.128
<i>♪ Don't know how it started ♪</i>

1618
01:00:22.197 --> 01:00:26.302
<i>♪ And I don't know
How it will end ♪</i>

1619
01:00:28.936 --> 01:00:31.103
This is the last time
you're picking the restaurant.

1620
01:00:31.172 --> 01:00:34.239
If they're gonna plaster
your life in the newspaper.

1621
01:00:34.308 --> 01:00:36.776
you would think they would
at least run a decent picture.

1622
01:00:36.844 --> 01:00:39.378
especially next to that Crystal.

1623
01:00:39.447 --> 01:00:42.616
Shouldn't she have a permit
to wear a dress like that?

1624
01:00:42.684 --> 01:00:45.585
You're awfully quiet
for a change.

1625
01:00:45.654 --> 01:00:47.991
Oh. Tough day at work is all.

1626
01:00:48.990 --> 01:00:51.424
<i>♪ Since you Can barely feel... ♪</i>

1627
01:00:51.493 --> 01:00:53.326
She's here.

1628
01:00:53.395 --> 01:00:54.526
Hi.

1629
01:00:53.395 --> 01:00:54.526
MARY: Hi.

1630
01:00:54.595 --> 01:00:56.329
Alex picked the restaurant.
right?

1631
01:00:56.398 --> 01:00:57.730
Uh...

1632
01:00:56.398 --> 01:00:57.730
Of course.

1633
01:00:57.799 --> 01:00:58.731
That looks good.

1634
01:00:58.800 --> 01:01:00.937
[MOUTHS] <i>Okay.</i>

1635
01:01:03.872 --> 01:01:05.171
So everybody's seen it. right?

1636
01:01:05.240 --> 01:01:08.107
Okay. No big elephants
on the table.

1637
01:01:08.176 --> 01:01:11.644
Just when you thought it
couldn't get any shittier.

1638
01:01:11.713 --> 01:01:12.979
Okay.

1639
01:01:11.713 --> 01:01:12.979
EDIE: Wanna have a big laugh

1640
01:01:13.048 --> 01:01:15.848
about it right now. huh?
Huh? Huh?

1641
01:01:15.917 --> 01:01:17.216
Or do you wanna run off
with a woman?

1642
01:01:17.285 --> 01:01:18.918
If you did.
this would be the place.

1643
01:01:18.986 --> 01:01:21.220
Well. maybe a margarita
and a woman.

1644
01:01:21.289 --> 01:01:22.955
Ooh. I like that.

1645
01:01:23.024 --> 01:01:24.724
I think it's gonna be okay.
ladies.

1646
01:01:24.793 --> 01:01:26.891
She's turned the page.

1647
01:01:26.960 --> 01:01:29.298
Yeah. I've turned the page.
I hired a lawyer today.

1648
01:01:32.500 --> 01:01:36.670
Mary. um... Don't you think maybe
it's too soon for lawyers?

1649
01:01:36.738 --> 01:01:38.905
Let things...
Let things settle down.

1650
01:01:38.973 --> 01:01:41.341
A month from now.
everything could look different.

1651
01:01:41.409 --> 01:01:43.209
What?

1652
01:01:41.409 --> 01:01:43.209
I... I know.

1653
01:01:43.278 --> 01:01:45.211
Okay. I'm gonna...
I'm gonna take a risk here

1654
01:01:45.280 --> 01:01:49.085
and... And say something
that maybe...

1655
01:01:49.918 --> 01:01:51.487
There are two sides
to every story.

1656
01:01:52.621 --> 01:01:54.053
Any one of us is capable.

1657
01:01:54.122 --> 01:01:55.955
under the right circumstances.

1658
01:01:56.024 --> 01:01:59.725
of making a very big mistake.

1659
01:01:59.794 --> 01:02:02.728
Right? Right?

1660
01:02:02.796 --> 01:02:08.167
And a good marriage counselor
might ask.

1661
01:02:08.236 --> 01:02:10.937
"And how were you culpable
in this marriage?"

1662
01:02:11.006 --> 01:02:13.506
Well. I married an asshole.
that's how I'm culpable.

1663
01:02:13.575 --> 01:02:14.908
Which side are you on?

1664
01:02:14.976 --> 01:02:16.710
I'm not taking sides.

1665
01:02:14.976 --> 01:02:16.710
Well. pick one.

1666
01:02:16.778 --> 01:02:18.247
Pick a side.

1667
01:02:16.778 --> 01:02:18.247
I'm on your side.

1668
01:02:19.747 --> 01:02:20.847
My money's on you.

1669
01:02:20.916 --> 01:02:22.682
All right. Okay.

1670
01:02:22.751 --> 01:02:24.216
[SIGHS]

1671
01:02:24.285 --> 01:02:26.185
Here's what I want to know.
I want to know how somebody

1672
01:02:26.253 --> 01:02:28.254
like Bailey Smith faces herself
in the mirror.

1673
01:02:28.322 --> 01:02:31.123
I wanna know how somebody
can make a living

1674
01:02:31.192 --> 01:02:32.859
feeding off of somebody else's
pain.

1675
01:02:32.927 --> 01:02:35.131
Mary. it's my fault.

1676
01:02:36.665 --> 01:02:38.001
Okay.

1677
01:02:39.200 --> 01:02:41.200
Bailey Smith knew
I was about to be fired.

1678
01:02:41.269 --> 01:02:44.036
and she knew that I needed her
on the magazine.

1679
01:02:44.105 --> 01:02:46.172
so she practically
blackmailed me.

1680
01:02:46.240 --> 01:02:48.041
I didn't give her
any information. She...

1681
01:02:48.109 --> 01:02:49.743
She had all the details already.

1682
01:02:49.811 --> 01:02:51.611
She just said.
"Nod if it's true."

1683
01:02:51.680 --> 01:02:53.549
and that's all I did. is nod.

1684
01:02:55.951 --> 01:02:57.717
I was in a terrible position.

1685
01:02:57.786 --> 01:03:00.119
I... I was scared.

1686
01:03:00.188 --> 01:03:02.655
You know. people do terrible
things when they're scared.

1687
01:03:02.724 --> 01:03:03.690
[SOBS]

1688
01:03:03.758 --> 01:03:05.292
And this is terrible.

1689
01:03:05.361 --> 01:03:06.326
I know that.

1690
01:03:06.394 --> 01:03:07.330
I know.

1691
01:03:09.631 --> 01:03:11.564
What is going on with you?

1692
01:03:11.633 --> 01:03:13.333
Uh... Uh...

1693
01:03:13.402 --> 01:03:14.367
Guys. I've been...

1694
01:03:14.435 --> 01:03:16.802
I'm f... I'm fighting
for a job that I've...

1695
01:03:16.871 --> 01:03:19.442
I've worked for my whole life.

1696
01:03:25.280 --> 01:03:28.881
<i>♪ 'Cause everything good goes ♪</i>

1697
01:03:28.950 --> 01:03:31.354
<i>♪ Away ♪</i>

1698
01:03:34.255 --> 01:03:36.155
What was it that you said.
Sylvie?

1699
01:03:36.224 --> 01:03:39.125
You said that betrayal is
inevitable in any relationship?

1700
01:03:39.194 --> 01:03:41.495
I thought you were just talking
about marriage.

1701
01:03:41.563 --> 01:03:42.762
This is so much worse.

1702
01:03:42.831 --> 01:03:47.170
<i>♪ raisin' the stakes ♪</i>

1703
01:03:49.304 --> 01:03:53.340
<i>♪ 'Cause everything good goes ♪</i>

1704
01:03:53.409 --> 01:03:55.475
<i>♪ Away ♪</i>

1705
01:03:55.544 --> 01:03:56.843
<i>♪ Hey ♪</i>

1706
01:03:56.911 --> 01:03:58.578
CRYSTAL:
<i>You don't have what it takes</i>

1707
01:03:58.647 --> 01:04:00.012
<i>to run a company like this.</i>

1708
01:04:00.081 --> 01:04:02.448
<i>Now take a walk
and never look back.</i>

1709
01:04:02.516 --> 01:04:05.521
<i>My father will never let you
get away with this. Ramona.</i>

1710
01:04:06.655 --> 01:04:08.655
<i>I'm sleeping with your father.</i>

1711
01:04:08.723 --> 01:04:10.626
<i>[♪♪♪]</i>

1712
01:04:12.594 --> 01:04:14.397
[ANNOUNCER READING]

1713
01:04:15.764 --> 01:04:17.096
<i>And who knows...</i>

1714
01:04:17.164 --> 01:04:19.566
God's sakes.

1715
01:04:17.164 --> 01:04:19.566
<i>...moisture better than Dove?</i>

1716
01:04:19.635 --> 01:04:21.100
Middle of the afternoon.

1717
01:04:21.168 --> 01:04:24.203
Your daughter's gonna be home
from school any minute.

1718
01:04:24.271 --> 01:04:28.107
You want her to see her mother
in her bathrobe again? Huh?

1719
01:04:28.175 --> 01:04:31.645
I don't look at clocks anymore.
It's very liberating.

1720
01:04:31.713 --> 01:04:33.649
[PHONE RINGS]

1721
01:04:36.951 --> 01:04:39.519
[MUTTERING]

1722
01:04:39.588 --> 01:04:41.554
[SIGHS]

1723
01:04:41.623 --> 01:04:43.490
Haines residence.

1724
01:04:43.559 --> 01:04:45.825
Oh. hello.

1725
01:04:45.894 --> 01:04:47.594
[CHUCKLES] S-Sure.

1726
01:04:47.663 --> 01:04:49.762
I still recognize your voice.

1727
01:04:49.831 --> 01:04:50.830
[CHUCKLES]

1728
01:04:50.899 --> 01:04:52.165
And how about me?

1729
01:04:52.233 --> 01:04:55.435
Oh. holding down the fort.

1730
01:04:55.504 --> 01:04:57.070
Uh.

1731
01:04:57.138 --> 01:05:00.740
Uh. I'll... I'll s... I'll see
if she's still here.

1732
01:05:00.809 --> 01:05:02.742
It's Mr. Haines.
He's on the phone.

1733
01:05:02.811 --> 01:05:05.311
Ugh! Tell him I'm not here.

1734
01:05:05.380 --> 01:05:07.146
I'm a bad liar.
If... If I were any better.

1735
01:05:07.215 --> 01:05:08.881
I'd be embezzling from you.

1736
01:05:08.950 --> 01:05:10.850
I don't want to talk to him.
I'm busy.

1737
01:05:10.919 --> 01:05:14.053
Okay. look. I'm the housekeeper.

1738
01:05:14.122 --> 01:05:16.555
I cook. I clean. I run errands
and that's it.

1739
01:05:16.623 --> 01:05:19.759
I'm not your secretary. I'm not
your mother. I'm not your pal.

1740
01:05:19.828 --> 01:05:21.260
I'm not involved.

1741
01:05:21.329 --> 01:05:24.267
Now. you get over here
and take care of your business.

1742
01:05:27.369 --> 01:05:28.304
[SIGHS]

1743
01:05:30.604 --> 01:05:33.039
Hello. Stephen. I haven't talked
to the appraiser yet.

1744
01:05:33.108 --> 01:05:34.306
I'll do it next week.

1745
01:05:34.375 --> 01:05:36.476
[WHISPERING]
Let's go. Get out of here.

1746
01:05:36.545 --> 01:05:38.244
Oh.

1747
01:05:38.312 --> 01:05:43.116
Oh. Well. I'm sure she'd love
to carve a pumpkin with you.

1748
01:05:43.184 --> 01:05:44.649
Well. thank you
for the invitation.

1749
01:05:44.718 --> 01:05:48.821
but I think you two are... You'd
be better off on your own.

1750
01:05:48.890 --> 01:05:51.057
Because I wouldn't have
the first idea

1751
01:05:51.126 --> 01:05:53.826
how to be around you
right now. Stephen.

1752
01:05:53.895 --> 01:05:56.162
No. I already told you.
it's over.

1753
01:05:56.230 --> 01:05:59.335
No marriage counselor.
I'll have Molly call you.

1754
01:06:00.668 --> 01:06:01.637
Oh...

1755
01:06:03.939 --> 01:06:05.871
Oh. sweetie.

1756
01:06:05.940 --> 01:06:07.974
Oh. I am so sorry.

1757
01:06:08.043 --> 01:06:10.613
I didn't mean
for you to hear that.

1758
01:06:11.780 --> 01:06:13.749
Oh.

1759
01:06:16.585 --> 01:06:17.620
[SIGHS]

1760
01:06:19.220 --> 01:06:20.652
<i>[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]</i>

1761
01:06:20.721 --> 01:06:23.055
SYLVIE [OVER MACHINE]:
<i>Mary. I know you're there.</i>

1762
01:06:23.124 --> 01:06:24.724
<i>Why won't you return my calls?</i>

1763
01:06:24.793 --> 01:06:26.626
<i>We have to talk about this.</i>

1764
01:06:26.695 --> 01:06:28.194
<i>[MACHINE BEEPS]</i>

1765
01:06:28.263 --> 01:06:31.531
<i>Hey. it's bad form to screen
calls. Mary. Pick up.</i>

1766
01:06:31.600 --> 01:06:32.799
<i>Pick up.</i>

1767
01:06:32.867 --> 01:06:34.770
[♪♪♪]

1768
01:06:44.613 --> 01:06:46.515
[DOORBELL RINGS]

1769
01:07:13.941 --> 01:07:15.775
May I help you?

1770
01:07:13.941 --> 01:07:15.775
[SCREAMS. GASPS]

1771
01:07:15.844 --> 01:07:17.977
What do you think you're doing.

1772
01:07:18.046 --> 01:07:19.979
sneaking up on me like that?

1773
01:07:20.048 --> 01:07:21.380
What are you doing

1774
01:07:21.449 --> 01:07:23.249
casing the house
like a Jehovah's Witness?

1775
01:07:23.318 --> 01:07:25.351
I am looking for Mary. okay?

1776
01:07:25.419 --> 01:07:28.187
I've left her a lot of messages
and she hasn't called me back.

1777
01:07:28.255 --> 01:07:30.556
She's not here.

1778
01:07:28.255 --> 01:07:30.556
Where is she?

1779
01:07:30.625 --> 01:07:31.724
Out of town.

1780
01:07:31.793 --> 01:07:32.958
What about Molly?

1781
01:07:33.027 --> 01:07:34.326
Molly is at school.

1782
01:07:34.395 --> 01:07:36.729
That's where the kids go
during the week.

1783
01:07:36.798 --> 01:07:38.567
[CHUCKLES] Cute.

1784
01:07:39.333 --> 01:07:41.767
Are we done? I have a lot to do.

1785
01:07:41.835 --> 01:07:45.171
Besides. your Pradas
are wrecking my perennials.

1786
01:07:45.239 --> 01:07:47.543
[♪♪♪]

1787
01:08:03.625 --> 01:08:05.228
[BRAKES SCREECH]

