2047
01:19:15.464 --> 01:19:17.063
Excuse me.

2048
01:19:17.132 --> 01:19:20.267
Hi. I'm looking for my mother.
Catherine Frazier.

2049
01:19:20.336 --> 01:19:21.467
How's she doing?

2050
01:19:21.535 --> 01:19:24.504
She's still in some pain.
but that's to be expected.

2051
01:19:24.573 --> 01:19:26.839
She's in there.

2052
01:19:26.908 --> 01:19:29.145
Oh. thank you.

2053
01:19:26.908 --> 01:19:29.145
Right there.

2054
01:19:33.447 --> 01:19:36.316
NURSE: You know. it'll be nice
up in your room at this time...

2055
01:19:36.385 --> 01:19:37.650
Mom?

2056
01:19:37.719 --> 01:19:39.322
[GROANING]

2057
01:19:41.756 --> 01:19:42.922
WOMAN: Nurse.

2058
01:19:42.991 --> 01:19:44.458
NURSE:

2059
01:19:42.991 --> 01:19:44.458
Get you something for the pain.

2060
01:19:44.526 --> 01:19:45.725
Mom?

2061
01:19:44.526 --> 01:19:45.725
No.

2062
01:19:45.794 --> 01:19:47.327
Mary.

2063
01:19:47.396 --> 01:19:49.165
Over here.

2064
01:19:51.433 --> 01:19:52.999
Oh. Mom. Does it hurt?

2065
01:19:53.068 --> 01:19:56.736
I just spent thousands
of dollars to look rested.

2066
01:19:56.805 --> 01:19:59.606
Of course it hurts.

2067
01:19:59.675 --> 01:20:01.641
You look great.

2068
01:20:01.710 --> 01:20:02.909
Oh. thank you. thank you.

2069
01:20:02.977 --> 01:20:04.511
I just can't believe
you did this.

2070
01:20:04.580 --> 01:20:07.146
Have you looked around lately?

2071
01:20:07.215 --> 01:20:10.483
There are no 60-year-old women.

2072
01:20:10.552 --> 01:20:12.384
I was the only one left.

2073
01:20:12.453 --> 01:20:15.021
No. Mom. I'm happy
you did what you wanted to do.

2074
01:20:15.089 --> 01:20:17.657
Really. really.
What have you always said to me?

2075
01:20:17.726 --> 01:20:19.025
Don't look back. no regrets.

2076
01:20:19.094 --> 01:20:22.529
Uh. I'm so full of shit.

2077
01:20:22.598 --> 01:20:24.430
I have plenty of regrets.

2078
01:20:24.499 --> 01:20:29.205
I regret I never accomplished
anything of my own.

2079
01:20:30.772 --> 01:20:31.904
I was ambivalent.

2080
01:20:31.973 --> 01:20:36.312
And frankly. I wanted things.

2081
01:20:37.011 --> 01:20:40.246
A big house. beautiful clothes.

2082
01:20:40.315 --> 01:20:42.482
It was easier
to get status from your father

2083
01:20:42.551 --> 01:20:45.454
than to get it for myself.

2084
01:20:46.387 --> 01:20:48.821
I know I failed you
in a lot of ways. Mary.

2085
01:20:48.890 --> 01:20:52.259
But probably none more
than that.

2086
01:20:52.327 --> 01:20:54.197
No. Mom.

2087
01:20:55.163 --> 01:20:57.497
Do you wanna have
a little bit of tea there?

2088
01:20:57.566 --> 01:20:59.502
Thanks.

2089
01:21:01.336 --> 01:21:04.770
Well. I've been thinking
about going back to work.

2090
01:21:04.839 --> 01:21:05.938
Not for Dad.

2091
01:21:06.007 --> 01:21:08.308
I wanna design
my own collection.

2092
01:21:08.377 --> 01:21:09.909
Whoa.

2093
01:21:09.978 --> 01:21:10.943
What brought that on?

2094
01:21:11.012 --> 01:21:12.444
Hitting bottom.

2095
01:21:12.513 --> 01:21:15.348
Having nothing left to lose.
I highly recommend it.

2096
01:21:15.417 --> 01:21:16.615
Oh!

2097
01:21:16.683 --> 01:21:20.086
If it wouldn't blow out 80
stitches. I'd be smiling now.

2098
01:21:20.154 --> 01:21:22.788
I don't wanna take on
more than I can handle.

2099
01:21:22.857 --> 01:21:24.056
Just a small collection.

2100
01:21:24.125 --> 01:21:25.825
Where are you
going to get the money?

2101
01:21:25.894 --> 01:21:28.097
I'll find some backers.

2102
01:21:29.030 --> 01:21:30.530
What about my inheritance?

2103
01:21:30.599 --> 01:21:31.964
Oh. no. Mom.

2104
01:21:32.033 --> 01:21:33.933
I never did anything with it.

2105
01:21:34.002 --> 01:21:36.235
What could be a better
investment than you?

2106
01:21:36.304 --> 01:21:38.170
No. that's not why I came here.

2107
01:21:38.239 --> 01:21:41.244
Oh. please.
I'm in no condition to argue.

2108
01:21:41.910 --> 01:21:43.543
[LAUGHS]

2109
01:21:43.612 --> 01:21:46.145
You know something?

2110
01:21:46.214 --> 01:21:49.015
Someday. when I'm sitting here
with my head in a helmet.

2111
01:21:49.084 --> 01:21:52.085
I hope my daughter has
as much love for me

2112
01:21:52.153 --> 01:21:53.686
as I do for you right now.

2113
01:21:53.755 --> 01:21:55.321
Hm.

2114
01:21:55.389 --> 01:21:59.459
You are even more
full of shit than I am.

2115
01:21:59.527 --> 01:22:00.994
[BOTH LAUGH]

2116
01:21:59.527 --> 01:22:00.994
Yeah.

2117
01:22:01.062 --> 01:22:03.299
[♪♪♪]

2118
01:22:22.083 --> 01:22:24.353
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

2119
01:22:34.696 --> 01:22:37.997
Ned. please. Um. I know.

2120
01:22:38.065 --> 01:22:39.966
It's not the strongest issue
I've turned out.

2121
01:22:40.034 --> 01:22:43.169
but next month
is a whole different story.

2122
01:22:43.238 --> 01:22:47.339
Bailey Smith is writing a
profile on Christiane Amanpour.

2123
01:22:47.408 --> 01:22:51.180
and Alex Fisher is getting me
some advanced material on her...

2124
01:22:54.850 --> 01:22:57.383
Ned. you can't do this.

2125
01:22:57.451 --> 01:23:00.987
Nobody turns a magazine around
in... In under a year.

2126
01:23:01.055 --> 01:23:04.223
Just give me three more issues.
okay?

2127
01:23:04.291 --> 01:23:07.960
I have got this great idea.

2128
01:23:08.029 --> 01:23:10.930
How about we do a whole issue
on revenge?

2129
01:23:10.998 --> 01:23:12.666
How to get it.

2130
01:23:12.734 --> 01:23:14.100
who to stick it to.

2131
01:23:14.168 --> 01:23:17.102
um. the lost art
of holding a grudge.

2132
01:23:17.171 --> 01:23:20.105
How to construct
the perfect rumor.

2133
01:23:20.174 --> 01:23:24.676
Um. the 10 best random acts
of getting even.

2134
01:23:24.745 --> 01:23:29.416
And we'll put a hot young
actress on the cover.

2135
01:23:29.485 --> 01:23:30.753
Yes.

2136
01:23:33.054 --> 01:23:34.987
Thank you.

2137
01:23:35.056 --> 01:23:38.491
Yeah. I think
it'll be brilliant too.

2138
01:23:38.560 --> 01:23:40.529
Okay. then.

2139
01:23:41.796 --> 01:23:43.699
I'll see you in the morning.

2140
01:23:47.836 --> 01:23:50.670
Hello?

2141
01:23:50.739 --> 01:23:51.938
Hello?

2142
01:23:52.007 --> 01:23:54.407
Molly?

2143
01:23:54.475 --> 01:23:56.442
Where is everybody?
Where is everybody?

2144
01:23:56.510 --> 01:23:58.777
MAGGIE: Here.

2145
01:23:56.510 --> 01:23:58.777
Oh. Hey. Oh. Maggie.

2146
01:23:58.846 --> 01:24:02.281
All that fabric from Italy?
The whole dye lot was off.

2147
01:24:02.349 --> 01:24:04.349
I had to completely re-cut

2148
01:24:02.349 --> 01:24:04.349
a pattern

2149
01:24:04.418 --> 01:24:05.884
and the fit model
didn't show up.

2150
01:24:05.953 --> 01:24:09.755
But it is going to be good.
Maggie. it's gonna be so good.

2151
01:24:09.824 --> 01:24:12.295
Where's Molly?

2152
01:24:09.824 --> 01:24:12.295
She's out there.

2153
01:24:14.229 --> 01:24:15.494
What is she doing?

2154
01:24:15.562 --> 01:24:19.435
Well. she says
she doesn't want to be a woman.

2155
01:24:24.872 --> 01:24:26.742
Hey. Mol.

2156
01:24:28.476 --> 01:24:29.741
Wow.

2157
01:24:29.810 --> 01:24:33.212
You've got quite
a little bonfire going there.

2158
01:24:33.281 --> 01:24:34.914
I started it off
with the slenders

2159
01:24:34.983 --> 01:24:36.883
and now I'm adding the supers.

2160
01:24:36.952 --> 01:24:39.322
That's the trick.

2161
01:24:41.657 --> 01:24:42.721
Well...

2162
01:24:42.790 --> 01:24:45.791
Wouldn't it be just great
if when you're born.

2163
01:24:45.860 --> 01:24:47.093
they give you a rule book.

2164
01:24:47.161 --> 01:24:48.928
so every time you came up
against something

2165
01:24:48.997 --> 01:24:51.430
you had no idea how to handle.

2166
01:24:51.499 --> 01:24:54.666
you just look it up in the book
and there'd be the answer?

2167
01:24:54.735 --> 01:24:59.939
You know. I used to feel sorry
for the kids in my class.

2168
01:25:00.008 --> 01:25:01.374
Every other weekend with Dad

2169
01:25:01.442 --> 01:25:03.375
until Mommy's boyfriend
sleeps over.

2170
01:25:03.444 --> 01:25:05.177
then Dad gets you two in a row.

2171
01:25:05.246 --> 01:25:07.780
I used to feel sorry for them.

2172
01:25:07.849 --> 01:25:09.585
Now I'm one of them.

2173
01:25:10.718 --> 01:25:14.319
Listen. Molly. I know that
I haven't been here for you.

2174
01:25:14.388 --> 01:25:17.656
And I'm very sorry about that.
We have a lot to talk about.

2175
01:25:17.725 --> 01:25:20.596
I can't talk to you
like I talk to Sylvie.

2176
01:25:22.430 --> 01:25:23.930
You've been talking to Sylvie?

2177
01:25:23.998 --> 01:25:25.564
She's been helping me.

2178
01:25:25.633 --> 01:25:29.068
Well. I wanna help you.
Why won't you let me help you?

2179
01:25:29.137 --> 01:25:30.302
Because all you'll do is tell me

2180
01:25:30.371 --> 01:25:32.672
that everything
is going to be fine.

2181
01:25:32.740 --> 01:25:34.040
and it's not.

2182
01:25:34.108 --> 01:25:37.310
Dad's living in an apartment
that barely has any furniture.

2183
01:25:37.378 --> 01:25:41.180
That Crystal woman
is coming over all the time.

2184
01:25:41.248 --> 01:25:43.282
She doesn't even call first.

2185
01:25:43.351 --> 01:25:45.718
Then she leaves stuff behind.

2186
01:25:45.787 --> 01:25:47.719
A dress. a purse.

2187
01:25:47.788 --> 01:25:50.756
I don't think he even really
likes her that much.

2188
01:25:50.825 --> 01:25:52.959
He's just lonely.

2189
01:25:53.027 --> 01:25:54.397
He misses you.

2190
01:25:55.262 --> 01:25:58.798
Molly. I can't.

2191
01:25:58.867 --> 01:26:00.403
I just can't.

2192
01:26:01.370 --> 01:26:03.469
I know. I remember.

2193
01:26:03.538 --> 01:26:06.739
I used to watch you get ready
to go out with Dad.

2194
01:26:06.807 --> 01:26:11.410
And you'd let me put on your
dresses and your high heels.

2195
01:26:11.478 --> 01:26:15.248
and draw on some lipstick.

2196
01:26:15.316 --> 01:26:16.920
I wanted to be you.

2197
01:26:22.090 --> 01:26:24.393
I'm gonna go call Sylvie.

2198
01:26:27.762 --> 01:26:29.128
[DOOR OPENS]

2199
01:26:29.197 --> 01:26:30.830
[SIGHS]

2200
01:26:29.197 --> 01:26:30.830
[DOOR CLOSES]

2201
01:26:30.899 --> 01:26:32.835
[♪♪♪]

2202
01:26:47.649 --> 01:26:49.115
Hey.

2203
01:26:49.183 --> 01:26:50.916
Hey.

2204
01:26:49.183 --> 01:26:50.916
Mary.

2205
01:26:50.985 --> 01:26:53.618
Hey. I wanna know what you're
talking to my daughter about.

2206
01:26:53.687 --> 01:26:55.721
I... I promised her
I wouldn't discuss it.

2207
01:26:55.790 --> 01:26:58.657
She's having emotional problems.
now you decide to be discreet?

2208
01:26:58.725 --> 01:27:00.626
Well. I... I thought she needed
a safe place.

2209
01:27:00.694 --> 01:27:04.797
I'm the safe place. okay?
That is my job. not yours.

2210
01:27:04.866 --> 01:27:06.332
I'm the mother. not you.

2211
01:27:06.401 --> 01:27:07.567
She said she loves me.

2212
01:27:07.636 --> 01:27:09.335
Yeah. you never have to say no.

2213
01:27:09.403 --> 01:27:10.770
You show me
the stretch marks. baby.

2214
01:27:10.839 --> 01:27:12.671
and you can do
all the mothering you want.

2215
01:27:12.739 --> 01:27:16.175
And what is this. casual Friday?
It's Wednesday.

2216
01:27:16.244 --> 01:27:17.276
Yeah. I know.

2217
01:27:17.344 --> 01:27:19.445
What's wrong?

2218
01:27:17.344 --> 01:27:19.445
Nothing.

2219
01:27:19.513 --> 01:27:22.481
Something.

2220
01:27:19.513 --> 01:27:22.481
Look. let's just drop it. okay?

2221
01:27:22.550 --> 01:27:25.351
I didn't mean to cause problems.
I was just trying to help.

2222
01:27:25.419 --> 01:27:28.024
Don't you ever
get tired of saying that?

2223
01:27:30.826 --> 01:27:31.824
[GASPS]

2224
01:27:31.893 --> 01:27:33.626
How dare you reprimand me
for stepping in

2225
01:27:33.694 --> 01:27:35.460
where you should have been
all along?

2226
01:27:35.529 --> 01:27:38.364
You have not been there
for your daughter. Mary.

2227
01:27:38.432 --> 01:27:39.664
You've not been there
for anybody.

2228
01:27:39.733 --> 01:27:41.567
How could you be.
when you're not willing

2229
01:27:41.635 --> 01:27:43.969
to face the hard stuff?

2230
01:27:41.635 --> 01:27:43.969
Don't you criticize me.

2231
01:27:44.038 --> 01:27:45.104
Let me ask you something.

2232
01:27:45.172 --> 01:27:46.372
Now that Molly trusts you.

2233
01:27:46.441 --> 01:27:48.507
are you gonna betray her
like you did me?

2234
01:27:48.575 --> 01:27:50.877
Do you have any idea how hard
it is to be your friend?

2235
01:27:50.946 --> 01:27:53.712
I tried to make it up to you.
What more do you want?

2236
01:27:53.781 --> 01:27:56.648
I wanna know how you can
sell out your best friend.

2237
01:27:56.717 --> 01:27:59.218
I hope that job
is worth it. Sylvie.

2238
01:27:59.287 --> 01:28:00.920
because it's all you've got.

2239
01:28:00.988 --> 01:28:02.254
I quit my job.

2240
01:28:02.323 --> 01:28:04.423
What?

2241
01:28:02.323 --> 01:28:04.423
What else could I do?

2242
01:28:04.492 --> 01:28:06.325
I was making
terrible compromises.

2243
01:28:06.393 --> 01:28:07.993
I can't believe you quit.

2244
01:28:08.061 --> 01:28:12.799
How could I be so out of whack
that I sold out my best friend?

2245
01:28:12.867 --> 01:28:15.368
Well. you were in
an impossible situation.

2246
01:28:15.436 --> 01:28:17.303
Of course you'd wanna
keep your job.

2247
01:28:17.372 --> 01:28:19.505
It's what you do.
and you're great at it.

2248
01:28:19.573 --> 01:28:22.241
Well. it's nothing compared to
being responsible for a child.

2249
01:28:22.310 --> 01:28:23.408
I don't know how you do it.

2250
01:28:23.477 --> 01:28:25.310
Come on. I'm a terrible mother.

2251
01:28:25.379 --> 01:28:27.346
Look what I'm passing down
from my own.

2252
01:28:27.415 --> 01:28:29.516
I can't even talk to
my own daughter about sex.

2253
01:28:29.585 --> 01:28:30.917
Well. it's easy for me.

2254
01:28:30.986 --> 01:28:33.252
I... I wasn't there changing
her diapers. I mean...

2255
01:28:33.321 --> 01:28:35.087
I know. you are helping me out.

2256
01:28:35.156 --> 01:28:38.090
You're doing me a really big
favor. Thank you very much.

2257
01:28:38.159 --> 01:28:40.529
Goddamn it. Thank you.

2258
01:28:41.463 --> 01:28:43.563
Anything I can do.

2259
01:28:43.632 --> 01:28:46.198
You have a huge job. huge.

2260
01:28:46.267 --> 01:28:47.932
I'm so glad
I never had children.

2261
01:28:48.001 --> 01:28:51.103
That's the last impermissible
thing you can say at a party.

2262
01:28:51.172 --> 01:28:52.738
that you don't want children.

2263
01:28:52.807 --> 01:28:56.241
Well. I'm gonna have a dinner
party and then you can say that.

2264
01:28:56.310 --> 01:28:58.811
Oh. my God. I'm exhausted.

2265
01:28:58.880 --> 01:28:59.879
Oh...

2266
01:28:59.948 --> 01:29:02.585
Oh. we're a mess.

2267
01:29:04.520 --> 01:29:06.855
I like your hair. though.

2268
01:29:07.422 --> 01:29:08.992
[BOTH SNICKER]

2269
01:29:17.365 --> 01:29:19.002
BOTH: Oh...

2270
01:29:21.069 --> 01:29:23.870
You know what?
I got my divorce papers today.

2271
01:29:23.938 --> 01:29:24.604
Oh.

2272
01:29:24.673 --> 01:29:27.373
All I have to do is sign.

2273
01:29:27.442 --> 01:29:31.243
and I can't seem to be able
to find a pen.

2274
01:29:31.312 --> 01:29:33.079
Mary. look.
it's the 21st century.

2275
01:29:33.147 --> 01:29:37.617
It's okay for people to fight
for their relationships.

2276
01:29:37.686 --> 01:29:39.718
You know what this feels like?

2277
01:29:39.786 --> 01:29:42.887
It feels like that...
That phantom limb syndrome.

2278
01:29:42.956 --> 01:29:45.324
You know that thing where
you lose a part of your body.

2279
01:29:45.392 --> 01:29:46.725
like an arm or something.

2280
01:29:46.794 --> 01:29:50.529
but you still have the sensation
that it's there?

2281
01:29:50.598 --> 01:29:52.932
Well. you know. I'm sure
Stephen feels the same way.

2282
01:29:53.001 --> 01:29:55.635
Oh. no. I'm not talking
about Stephen and me.

2283
01:29:55.704 --> 01:29:58.641
I'm talking about you and me.

2284
01:30:00.842 --> 01:30:01.945
Oh.

2285
01:30:07.014 --> 01:30:08.282
BOTH: Oh...

2286
01:30:08.350 --> 01:30:10.384
[♪♪♪]

2287
01:30:10.452 --> 01:30:12.621
Fan out.

2288
01:30:22.263 --> 01:30:23.696
Hi. remember me?

2289
01:30:23.765 --> 01:30:25.831
Oh. Mrs. Haines.

2290
01:30:23.765 --> 01:30:25.831
My nails are a mess.

2291
01:30:25.899 --> 01:30:28.267
But why wouldn't they be.
with what I've been through?

2292
01:30:28.335 --> 01:30:30.269
Do you have time?

2293
01:30:28.335 --> 01:30:30.269
No problem.

2294
01:30:30.338 --> 01:30:33.006
It's the least I could do.

2295
01:30:33.074 --> 01:30:34.406
Mary?

2296
01:30:33.074 --> 01:30:34.406
Sylvie.

2297
01:30:34.475 --> 01:30:36.910
Oh. hi. how have you been?

2298
01:30:36.978 --> 01:30:37.844
Oh. fantastic.

2299
01:30:37.913 --> 01:30:40.680
I just had
the most fabulous facial.

2300
01:30:40.749 --> 01:30:43.382
So how's it going with
you-know-who?

